body: We want to provide some status messages in the inspector panel while downloading JxBrowser files or while starting DevTools. The paths once a project is run: - FlutterView::debugActiveHelper - JxBrowser is not enabled -> skip to normal inspector - JxBrowser is installed -> `handleJxBrowserInstalled` (show that devtools is starting) - JxBrowser installation failed -> `handleJxBrowserInstallationFailed` (offer user option to retry installation) - JxBrowser installation is in progress -> `handleJxBrowserInstallationInProgress` (wait for installation) - Success -> `handleJxBrowserInstalled` - Failure -> `handleJxBrowserInstallationFailed` - Time out -> Show error message Messages will be shown in the panel, e.g.:

comment_data.body: you should listen for an event from JxBrowserManager indicating that installation succeeded or failed rather than sleeping.
I believe there is a JBLink or similar class that is already styled to look like a link. I think the performance tab sohws an example of using it.
you could also use CompletableFuture completing the future when JxBrowserManager is ready.
Would be good to avoid using sleep outside of tests. Remove this method.
is there a reason to not make this limit 10X higher? Users may have limited bandwidth.

I have no opinion on this and chose a random number. This doesn't end the download attempt, only the completable future, but since we display a message suggesting a restart we should probably just make this bigger.

This logic is only safe if waitForInstallation is called after setUp is called.
Here's a way to tweak it to make it a bit more robust.
Only create a new installation CompletableFuture if the previous future is already completed (indicates a previous failed install). Document he assumptions about the completed future.

why has the executeOnPolledThread call gone away?
The CompletableFuture code as written is still blocking but you could switch to the async version if you don't want to block.
Is my change and comment here accurate?
installation is never null. you could annotate it as non nullable.
nit: comment that you must call setup as well as calling this message or it will time out.
